To run this codes in ubuntu : 
  1) In ubuntu system , NASM should be installed if not put this commands - 
sudo apt -get update 
and then 
sudo apt -y install nasm
  2) save the text file with .asm extension  
  3) open the file location in ubuntu using cd command
  4) Then write these stataments 
-- nasm -f elf -o filename.o filename.asm         (This command is use to create object file)
-- ld -m elf_i386 -o filename filename.o          (This command is use to linking or to create executable file)
-- ./filename                                     (This command is to run the file

if you are intrested how this all codes works then gdb - general debugger commands are 
-- gdb filename
-- layout asm
-- layout regs
-- set disassembly-flavor inetl
-- break _start
-- run 
-- ni
